Lovely. See you then.

486
00:31:33,985 --> 00:31:36,322
Don't fret.
I wouldn't seduce you over a meal.

487
00:31:36,725 --> 00:31:38,566
That would be very sophomoric.

488
00:31:39,123 --> 00:31:41,129
I didn't think
you were trying to seduce me.

489
00:31:41,516 --> 00:31:44,025
Come on. How could that thought
not have entered your head?

490
00:31:46,170 --> 00:31:48,105
Your denial that it did intrigues me.

491
00:31:50,144 --> 00:31:51,162
Bite me.

492
00:31:59,546 --> 00:32:00,546
What is this?

493
00:32:06,546 --> 00:32:09,097
That's Van Pelt?
What is she doing?

494
00:32:14,645 --> 00:32:16,728
This is a live feed
from the Shand Creek restaurant,

495
00:32:16,889 --> 00:32:19,255
and this is
how we're gonna catch Melanie's killer.

496
00:32:38,741 --> 00:32:39,741
Say again.

497
00:32:40,296 --> 00:32:41,296
Nothing.

498
00:32:45,293 --> 00:32:46,217
I see you.

499
00:32:50,397 --> 00:32:52,557
- How do I look?
- Good. You look good.

500
00:32:53,114 --> 00:32:54,714
I meant, can you see the wire?

501
00:32:58,386 --> 00:32:59,386
<i>Nope. Nope.</i>

502
00:33:03,311 --> 00:33:05,653
The killer plans
to bring his victim back to this room.

503
00:33:05,946 --> 00:33:08,823
And when he does, we're gonna be here
to greet him. How sweet is that?

504
00:33:09,166 --> 00:33:12,683
This is all a big elaborate joke
you're gonna apologize for now.

505
00:33:13,237 --> 00:33:16,079
Whoever killed Melanie had to be there
that night at Shand Csreek.

506
00:33:16,199 --> 00:33:19,250
Your time line proves it. There's no way
anyone else could've done it.

507
00:33:19,637 --> 00:33:21,878
One of the 20 people there
that night killed Melanie.

508
00:33:22,511 --> 00:33:25,672
All 20 of those people
are there now today,

509
00:33:25,833 --> 00:33:28,832
- including the killer.
- And he's gonna try it again today?

510
00:33:29,217 --> 00:33:31,448
- Come on.
- No, yes, that's just the point.

511
00:33:31,568 --> 00:33:33,556
Yes, he is gonna try again.

512
00:33:35,134 --> 00:33:36,492
He's planning on it.

513
00:33:38,155 --> 00:33:40,964
And he's gonna try again today
because we are gonna make him try again

514
00:33:41,084 --> 00:33:43,516
because he's not
in control of his desires.

515
00:33:43,636 --> 00:33:46,611
He's been thinking of nothing else
but this perverse craving of his.

516
00:33:47,199 --> 00:33:50,490
He's gotten so close.
He's desperate to go all the way.

517
00:33:50,698 --> 00:33:54,088
All we need to do is present him
with something he can't resist,

518
00:33:54,208 --> 00:33:57,372
something that he will jump at,
and damn the consequences.

519
00:33:58,011 --> 00:34:00,708
Give it a try.
If I'm wrong, there's no harm down.

520
00:34:05,259 --> 00:34:06,275
It's fusion.

521
00:34:06,961 --> 00:34:08,137
Confusion.

522
00:34:09,384 --> 00:34:11,469
Up to me,
make it a cheeseburger every time.

523
00:34:12,510 --> 00:34:14,055
Me, too. With onion rings.

524
00:34:27,145 --> 00:34:28,493
- Let's do it.
- Not yet.

525
00:34:28,613 --> 00:34:30,947
- Why not?
- This is actually quite good.

526
00:34:37,485 --> 00:34:39,706
You're meant to shout at me
and leave.

527
00:34:43,995 --> 00:34:45,317
Now you've gone too far!

528
00:34:48,917 --> 00:34:50,134
I hate you!

529
00:35:01,951 --> 00:35:03,521
- Smooth work.
- Don't.

530
00:35:12,447 --> 00:35:14,115
Can I call you a cab?

531
00:35:14,388 --> 00:35:17,744
No, thank you. I need a walk.
I have a number for a cab if I need one.

532
00:35:18,479 --> 00:35:21,209
- Thank you for a delicious meal.
- Oh, you're so welcome.

533
00:35:39,551 --> 00:35:40,967
Just left the restaurant.

534
00:35:41,087 --> 00:35:42,977
<i>I'm heading towards the main road now.</i>

535
00:35:47,199 --> 00:35:48,940
<i>Sorry, miss.
I didn't see you there.</i>

536
00:35:49,101 --> 00:35:50,293
I was just...

537
00:35:50,868 --> 00:35:52,820
- You okay?
- Sure. Absolutely.

538
00:35:52,980 --> 00:35:54,447
<i>Just scared me a little.</i>

539
00:35:56,198 --> 00:35:57,263
He wasn't su...

540
00:35:58,148 --> 00:36:00,912
- What the hell is he doing there?
- He was there.

541
00:36:02,199 --> 00:36:03,504
He was there that night.

542
00:36:03,758 --> 00:36:04,883
<i>Going for a stroll?</i>

543
00:36:05,760 --> 00:36:06,760
Fresh air.

544
00:36:07,078 --> 00:36:08,564
Only you need to be careful.

545
00:36:08,970 --> 00:36:11,192
We've been looking for a murderer
loose around here.

546
00:36:12,570 --> 00:36:15,237
Went after a girl just like you...
Red hair and all.

547
00:36:15,759 --> 00:36:16,759
No kidding.

548
00:36:17,269 --> 00:36:19,402
I'll drive you up to the main road.

549
00:36:20,058 --> 00:36:21,163
Thank you, but...

550
00:36:22,448 --> 00:36:23,679
No trouble, really.

551
00:36:23,799 --> 00:36:25,379
My car's just over here on the side.

552
00:36:26,556 --> 00:36:28,272
- Please advise.
- Keep it rolling.

553
00:36:28,777 --> 00:36:29,816
Beg your pardon?

554
00:36:33,761 --> 00:36:35,462
I'm not used to wearing these shoes.

555
00:36:36,267 --> 00:36:39,534
- Are you out here alone?
- I had an argument with my date.

556
00:36:41,435 --> 00:36:43,829
<i>Sorry to hear that.
You know, if you were my date,</i>

557
00:36:44,130 --> 00:36:46,225
I wouldn't argue,
pretty lady like yourself.

558
00:36:46,914 --> 00:36:48,387
My car's just right over here.

559
00:36:49,642 --> 00:36:51,076
It's okay. I'll walk.

560
00:36:51,196 --> 00:36:53,275
Wait, no. I won't let you.

561
00:36:58,631 --> 00:37:01,597
Really, ma'am.
I don't feel comfortable letting you go.

562
00:37:02,105 --> 00:37:03,259
Really, I'm fine.

563
00:37:04,198 --> 00:37:05,713
I think you're intoxicated.

564
00:37:06,571 --> 00:37:08,482
- I am not.
- Get your hands off her!

565
00:37:09,935 --> 00:37:11,662
What the hell's the matter with you?!

566
00:37:11,926 --> 00:37:14,110
- You're under arrest!
- You're under arrest...

567
00:37:14,270 --> 00:37:15,422
- Calm down.
- Cho?

568
00:37:15,968 --> 00:37:17,351
Is this clown one of yours?

569
00:37:19,073 --> 00:37:21,993
- What the hell is going on here?
- Sheriff, everything okay?

570
00:37:23,184 --> 00:37:24,187
Now it is...

571
00:37:25,643 --> 00:37:27,123
<i>Suppose so. Barely.</i>

572
00:37:30,685 --> 00:37:33,137
- Everything's funny.
- Well, if you try.

573
00:37:33,330 --> 00:37:34,797
Come on. It's pretty funny.

574
00:37:35,848 --> 00:37:36,876
Strange, though.

575
00:37:37,477 --> 00:37:40,595
I was sure the chef would bite.
There's still a chance he could show up.

576
00:37:40,982 --> 00:37:42,227
The chef... Malcolm?

577
00:37:43,256 --> 00:37:44,678
Why do you think it's him?

578
00:37:45,296 --> 00:37:46,824
He uses way too much butter.

579
00:37:47,107 --> 00:37:48,738
- Say?
- He's a gluttonous baby.

580
00:37:48,858 --> 00:37:51,366
He's self-indulgent.
He wants what he wants and he takes it.

581
00:37:51,486 --> 00:37:52,971
Too much butter. - Yeah.

582
00:37:53,606 --> 00:37:55,484
It's fascinating
the way your mind works.

583
00:37:56,671 --> 00:37:59,468
One thing, though... Malcolm
was in the kitchen with 20 people

584
00:37:59,588 --> 00:38:01,799
when Melanie was taken.
He couldn't have done it.

585
00:38:01,919 --> 00:38:03,737
Hang on.
There's a way he could...

586
00:38:03,857 --> 00:38:06,230
Forgive me if I can't stay
for more of your theorizing,

587
00:38:06,350 --> 00:38:08,670
but I've gotta go
and see if I can save your colleagues

588
00:38:08,790 --> 00:38:10,901
from getting formal complaints
in their files.

589
00:38:25,830 --> 00:38:27,125
I'll be right there.

590
00:38:40,406 --> 00:38:41,549
I know where it is.

591
00:38:59,203 --> 00:39:00,841
Right here.
That's good.

592
00:39:02,733 --> 00:39:04,142
You're good.

593
00:39:06,006 --> 00:39:07,056
It's okay. Good.

594
00:39:24,232 --> 00:39:25,241
Quiet! Quiet!

595
00:39:40,261 --> 00:39:41,818
Help me put this on the bed.

596
00:39:55,044 --> 00:39:56,312
Stop. Think.

597
00:39:56,883 --> 00:39:59,358
Do not move.
Whatever you do, do not move.

598
00:39:59,765 --> 00:40:01,352
- What?
- Do not move!

599
00:40:05,298 --> 00:40:06,907
Stop! Come back here!

600
00:40:08,919 --> 00:40:11,204
- What are you doing here?
- Think.

601
00:40:12,134 --> 00:40:14,607
- What are you doing here?
- Does it matter? I'm here.

602
00:40:14,727 --> 00:40:17,260
This place is surrounded by police
and CBI agents.

603
00:40:18,990 --> 00:40:21,483
He's lying.
They would be up here arresting us

604
00:40:21,603 --> 00:40:23,335
- by now if they were here.
- S.W.A.T.

605
00:40:23,608 --> 00:40:26,260
They're waiting on S.W.A.T.
There's no way out of this.

606
00:40:29,231 --> 00:40:32,224
Nobody. Let's just kill them
and get out of here.

607
00:40:32,903 --> 00:40:35,583
Listen to me.
You can walk away from all of this.

608
00:40:36,013 --> 00:40:38,320
No disrespect,
but you're both clinically insane.

609
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:41,037
You're not gonna go to prison.
But to a hospital for a couple of years,

610
00:40:41,157 --> 00:40:43,319
- and you can walk away.
- Shut up! Just shut up!

611
00:40:43,908 --> 00:40:46,322
- I'm trying to think.
- Now he's trying to think!

612
00:40:46,482 --> 00:40:49,098
Don't pretend you didn't want this.
You wanted it just as much as me!

613
00:40:49,218 --> 00:40:51,842
I told you we didn't have enough time.
I told you...

614
00:40:51,962 --> 00:40:54,245
- One more word out of you!
- Don't you point that at me!

615
00:40:54,762 --> 00:40:55,748
Police!

616
00:40:59,862 --> 00:41:00,878
Put the gun down!

617
00:41:16,856 --> 00:41:18,395
You're gonna be fine, all right?

618
00:41:22,515 --> 00:41:24,401
We're gonna get you out of here.

619
00:41:41,239 --> 00:41:42,418
I don't get it.

620
00:41:42,833 --> 00:41:45,271
She actually enjoyed helping him kill.

621
00:41:45,820 --> 00:41:48,134
One crazy evil person, I understand.

622
00:41:48,728 --> 00:41:50,177
But two? Husband and wife?

623
00:41:51,854 --> 00:41:55,371
Marriage is supposed to be a sacred,
loving thing.

624
00:41:56,629 --> 00:41:59,144
They were soul mates
in their own strange way.

625
00:42:01,848 --> 00:42:02,848
Let's go.

